# SEO Guidelines

## Keyword Research
- Use tools like Google Keyword Planner, Ahrefs, or SEMrush to identify relevant keywords related to AI tutorials.
- Focus on long-tail keywords such as "how to use AI for image recognition" or "AI tutorial for beginners" to target specific queries.

## On-Page SEO
- Ensure each page has a unique and descriptive title tag and meta description that includes target keywords.
- Use headings (H1, H2, H3) effectively to structure content and include keywords naturally.
- Write high-quality, informative content that answers users' questions and provides value. Avoid keyword stuffing.

## Technical SEO
- Optimize the website for fast loading times using tools like Google PageSpeed Insights.
- Ensure the site is mobile-friendly, as Google uses mobile-first indexing.
- Use clean and descriptive URLs that include keywords.

## Content Strategy
- Regularly update content to reflect the latest AI trends and technologies.
- Use internal links to connect related content on the site, aiding navigation for both users and search engines.

## Backlinks
- Acquire quality backlinks from reputable sites in the AI and tech industry through guest blogging, partnerships, or creating shareable content.
- Promote tutorials on social media platforms to increase visibility and drive traffic.

## Schema Markup
- Implement schema markup to help search engines understand content better and enhance search result listings with rich snippets.

## Analytics and Monitoring
- Use Google Search Console to monitor site performance in search results and identify issues.
- Use tools like Google Analytics to track user behavior and optimize content strategy based on data insights. 